4.3.3.3
Radiological Releases
In 2000, an estimated 431 curies of tritium, 0.32 curies of plutonium-239/240, and 0.049 curies of americium-241 were released to the atmosphere at NTS.
These releases were attributed to the diffusion of tritiated (tritium) water vapor from evaporation from tunnel and characterization well containment ponds; diffuse emissions calculated from the results of environmental surveillance activities; and the resuspension of plutonium and americium as measured with air sampling equipment or calculated by use of resuspension equations.
