These doses fall within the radiological regulatory limits of 10 CFR 835.
According to a risk estimator of one latent fatal cancer per 2,500 person-rem among workers (see Appendix B), the number of projected fatal cancers among NTS workers from normal operations in 2001 is 5.2 Ã— 10-4.
The risk estimator for workers is lower than the estimator for the public because of the absence from the workforce of the more radiosensitive infant and child age groups.
